description:
{This algorithm explores the search space using a Simulated Annealing framework where the "temperature" and
perturbation scale adapt based on the acceptance rate of new solutions and recent improvements,
periodically performing wider random jumps to escape deep local optima.}

{This algorithm evolves a probability distribution over the search space, from which new solutions are sampled;
the distribution's mean is derived from the best current solutions (elites), and its standard deviation
adaptively contracts for exploitation upon progress or expands for exploration upon stagnation.}

{The algorithm maintains a swarm of particles, each adaptively probing its neighborhood in directions 
influenced by its personal best, the global best, and random exploration, with periodic diversification 
of stagnant particles to prevent premature convergence.}

{This algorithm performs local exploration by sampling new candidate solutions from a Gaussian distribution centered 
at the current best solution, adaptively adjusting the standard deviation (search scale) based on improvement, 
and initiating global random jumps upon sustained stagnation to escape local optima.}

A self-adaptive Differential Evolution algorithm dynamically generating mutation and crossover parameters 
from successful historical values, periodically employing a focused local search around promising solutions, 
and initiating an exploratory restart for a portion of the population upon stagnation.
